Are you able to reproduce this consistently?

Please zip up your configuration directory and attach it.  The configuration/ directory is located in your eclipse install directory by default.

The resolver cache looks ok in the configuration.  From the stacktrace it looked like there was a corrupted cache.  The zipfile you attached is missing some files though.  I would expect to see a directory "configuration/org.eclipse.osgi/.manager".  Does this directory exist in your configuration?  Are you still seeing this error after you restart?

One thing I did notice is that there are two versions of the framework cache.  This occurs when you have multiple instances of eclipse running and one instance modifies the set of installed bundles (install/uninstall features etc.).  We keep the old version of the cache on disk until all instances of eclipse are closed which use the cache.  The latest version of the cache has about half the number of bundles as the previous cache.  Did you recently uninstall some features when this error started to occur?
I don't see this error anymore it just stopped after couple of days, which probably indicates that your cache theory is right.
